The paper deals with information theory and its applications to network information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.MS (Mathematical Optimization) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The mention of functional inequalities could suggest cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
